6 An Act relating to highway remediation services;
requiring highway remediation and cleanup services
7 maintain certain minimum liability insurance
coverage; requiring coverage for licensure;
8 authorizing certain suspension or revocation of
license; requiring certain price list be published on
9 website; requiring annual update of price list;
listing requirements of price list; providing for
10 codification; and providing an effective date.
11
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
15 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 2-7-407 of Title 27A, unless
16 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
17 Every highway remediation and cleanup service operating within
18 this state shall maintain commercial general liability insurance
19 coverage of not less than Three Million Dollars ($3,000,000.00),
20 that includes completed operations and pollution liability coverage.
21 Proof of such coverage shall be provided upon licensure by the
22 Department of Environmental Quality and upon request to law
23 enforcement, the Department of Transportation, insurers, or
24 contracting parties. The Department of Environmental Quality may
ENGR. H. B. NO. 3297 Page 1

1 susp end or revoke the license of a highway remediation and cleanup
2 service for failure to maintain the coverage required pursuant to
3 this section.
4 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
5 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 2-7-408 of Title 27A, unless
6 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
7 Each highway remediation and cleanup service operating in this
8 state shall publish and maintain on a publicly accessible website a
9 clear, searchable price list of its top fifty (50) most frequently
10 billed nonconsent highway remediation services. The price list
11 shall be updated at least annually and made available prior to or
12 contemporaneously with billing. The price list shall include, at a
13 minimum:
14 1. A plain-language description of each service;
15 2. The standard charge for each service, including, but not
16 limited to, hourly rates, common equipment charges, and emergency
17 surcharges;
18 3. Units of measurement or billing increments; and
19 4. Any commonly applied surcharges.
20 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
